review_blob: Wonderfully hoppy.  I love trying new Stone beers, and am glad I took a chance on this.
Im not a fan of lagers,but a friend left this in the fridge.  Nothing bad here, but nothing special. I would rather have a Heineken if going for a beer like this.
12 oz bottle.  I expected more of an IPA taste with this one, based on a friends recommendation.  Some citrus, a lacy head, looks great, tastes like a weak IPA.  Ill recommend, but not strongly.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Not bad for a grocery store IPA.  It has a nice, hoppy aroma with a pleasant citrus taste.  An average, but good IPA
22 bottle.  Had a nice head, and a great hoppy aroma.  Good Beer, a definite recommendation for someone looking for an IPA
Had a big bottle at Stir-Fry in Johnson City, TN.  Smelled great with a nice citrus nose, nice blend of hops.  Great with sushi!

Pretty solid IPA.  Orange color with good head retention. Taste is hoppy, but not very bitter.  I actually prefer a little more bittterness with an IPA, so the overall rating is lowered to reflect that.  Overall, a good beer Ill probably buy again.
12 oz bottle.  Pours a bright, darker shade of orange.  Sweet and fruity hopped aroma, but not overpowering. A good IPA
Eh...not much here. Looks good on the pour, but the head was huge.  Tasted sour and sudsy.   Yuk

12oz bottle.   Ok, so Im new to Imperial/Double IPAs, and I really couldnt get behind this one. It looked good out of the bottle, smelled strong of grapefruit and other citrus, but the flavor just seemed "off".  Ill keep trying, but I may stick with regular IPAs, which seem more to my palate.
Growler from Libation Station.  Good, not too hoppy IPA shared with friends at a cookout. One of the better IPAs Ive had in a while.
Pretty good IPA.  Was expecting more hops from this one, especially from the high ratings.  A good, not overpowering IPA.  Actually got better as the glass emptied.
Pours dark gold  with tan head. Slight aroma of grass and grapefruit.  Pretty good IPA.
Pours light amber with a 1 inch frothy head.  Aroma of grapefruit and other citrus.  Not as hoppy as some IPAs but a very smooth drink.  Top notch.
On Tap at Kingsport Grocery Company. Pours black as midnight with a beautiful tan head.  Very smooth. One of my favorite stouts.
On tap at the Kingsport Grocery.  Earthy aroma, with hints of citrus.  Not my favorite IPAs, but the best of the Depot Street beers Ive tried.

Wow.   Limited Spring 2009 release.  Pours black and thick...absolutely beautiful.  Aroma of dark roast, caramel, banana.  Coffee taste comes out at the end of a drink.  Best Imperial Stout Ive tried.  Kudos.

12oz bottle.  Pours a dark brown with very little head.  Nose of chococate and roasted coffee.  Halfway thru the glass, the coffee aroma became more pronounced.  Not my favorite porter, but well done.  Tasty.
My first premium Belgian ale, so Im not sure what to compare it to.  Pours dirty brown with very little head.  Pleasant amount of carbonation.  Fruit aroma in there...banana?   Good beer.

This is one that I sought out, as its not available around East Tennessee.  Somewhat disappointed, as I was expecting a hoppier taste.  Almost a flat flavor when opened, with practically no head.  Looked good in the glass, though.  Not a bad beer...just something i may need to try again.

Bought this for my wife, since she only likes fruity beers, but I ended up drinking it.  Superior aroma with the grapes and honey to the front.  Very smooth on the palate. The higher ABV was barely noticable.  Careful with this one!  Youll be hooked.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: Finally tried one of these in bottle a few weeks ago.  Probably the first Imperial I can remember, and it was a great one.  Maybe a little strong, but i can see why the ratings are so high.  Will try again for sure.
Decent beer if its on tap and there isnt much else to choose from.  Better than most domestic macros.  Looks good on the pour, but disappoints in the palate with a watery taste.

Another good beer from Ashevilles Highland brewery. Looks and smells fantastic, with just enough fruity notes.  However, something is missing that I cant quite put my finger on to raise the overall score.
Aroma of citrus and a little pine.  Pours with small white head.  A very good IPA. Not the hoppiest Ive had, but a good choice on tap or bottle.
This is one of the first craft beers I tried, and is still a favorite.  Goes great with pizza and burgers.  Has a nice amount of hops, without getting into IPA territory.
Dark and robust, with a nice medium tan head.  A really good porter both on tap and in bottles.
An easy drinking Summer Ale, with a hint on Honey and Orange.  Weaker than I expected.  Wouldnt recommend it to friends.
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: Not bad for a mass produced Witbier.  I usually get one if its the only "craft" beer at the restaurant, or if its on special on tap.
Terrible beer.  Ugly to look at and even worse to smell.  Typical Miller beer.
One opf my favorite fruit beers. A little too much carbonation taste, but a nice raspberry flavor. Nice on a hot day.
UPDATED: MAR 10, 2010
Bottle.  Pours nicely with a good floral nose.  Goes down smooth.  A real treat.
